  "text": "15.2 A Structure-Centered Approach 15.2.1 A Whorfian Approach: From Language to Reality Contemporary research into the influence of language type on thought takes the work of Benjamin Lee [CITATION_1] as its point of departurewhether or not the actual substance and significance of that work are well understood by those who invoke it. This is not the place to revisit Whorf's arguments in detail (for that see [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ), but one key aspect, namely, his views about the mutual relation of language and reality, deserves mention since it lies at the heart of his comparative approach and motivates the one developed here.",
